e, I know that my father, who has actually published an (Indian) English book, was faulted on his speaking exam when applying to become a doctor in the US for putting the "wrong" stress on words like "inundated." Not only is the prescriptive nature of this test troubling, it seems curious why it would be relevant to his ability to practice medicine in any case.%0a%3c %0a%3c [1] https://news.nau.edu/kang-english-accents/#.YIzOS6lKgTU%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
